cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "RadiativeViewFactor.jl"
message: >-
  If you use this software in your research, please cite it using
  the metadata from this file.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Coxe
    given-names: Alex
    email: rot4te@gmail.com
    orcid: ""
repository-code: "https://github.com/rot4te/RadiativeViewFactor.jl"
url: "https://rot4te.github.io/RadiativeViewFactor.jl"
abstract: >-
  A Julia package for computing radiative view factors between arbitrary
  surfaces or curves discretized on 2nd-order meshes generated with Gmsh.
  Supports Gauss-Legendre quadrature, Monte Carlo integration with stratified
  sampling, and the Sauter-Schwab Duffy transformation for near-singular
  element pairs. Provides CPU multi-threading and GPU backends (NVIDIA CUDA
  and Apple Metal) via KernelAbstractions.jl, with BVH-accelerated obstruction
  detection on all backends.
keywords:
  - julia
  - radiation
  - view factor
  - configuration factor
  - finite element
  - monte carlo
  - GPU
  - heat transfer
